The paper deals with transportation polytopes in the probability simplex, which are related to information theory and machine learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves studying mappings between polytopes, which can be seen as a problem in computational geometry, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves probability distributions and sets, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
